



Sir

th feb 7 1782




Agreable to Yor Excellencys permission, I took the Liberty to introdce by those few Lines Monsr. Girad the painter who copied the greatest Genal. of this age for me,1 may he be favourd to procre me the pourtret of the greatest American Minister in that of yor Excellency; it will add to the obligation yor Excellency conferred on s.2 Begging leave to assre your Excellency of the highest regards with which I have the honor to be sir! Yor Excellencys most obed & humb servt.

John de Neufville

